The API returns a list (array) like this:
[
  {
    "_id": "s1",
    "nomsal": "Alami",
    "prenomsal": "Sara",
    "fonction": "Technicien",
    "service": {
      "codeser": "1",
      "nomser": "informatique"
    }
  }
]
🧠 Meaning of each field

For each employee:

_id → unique ID
nomsal → last name
prenomsal → first name
fonction → job (Technicien, etc.)
service → object that contains:
codeser → service code
nomser → service name (e.g. informatique)

What you should do in React?

   You should start with creat "State"
const [salaries, setSalaries] = useState([]); then 
Call the API when the component loads


the full code:
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";

function App() {
  const [salaries, setSalaries] = useState([]);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("http://localhost:8000/salaries")
      .then((res) => res.json())
      .then((data) => {
        setSalaries(data);
      })
      .catch((err) => console.log(err));
  }, []);

  return (
    <div>
      {salaries.map((sal) => (
        <div key={sal._id}>
          <p>{sal.nomsal} {sal.prenomsal}</p>
          <p>{sal.fonction}</p>
          <p>{sal.service.nomser}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
 In simple words
  -The backend gives you a list of employees
  -You fetch it using GET
  -You store it in salaries state
  -Then you display it in your app

